casebody.data:
ADAM BROWN, Plaintiff and Appellant, v. SIGMUND P. WINDMULLER et al., Defendants and Respondents.

Before Barbour, Ch. J., Monell and Van Vorst, JJ.

Decided January 4, 1873. Appeal from an order of Special Term denying motion to set aside referee’s report. Andrew H. H. Dawson, for appellant. James Taylor, for respondent. Order affirmed.

No opinion rendered.
